### 2. Version Comparison and Reversion

**Description**:  
This pattern leverages Git's ability to compare different versions of code (`git diff`) and revert to previous states (`git revert` or `git reset`) to isolate and resolve issues. It is particularly useful in complex debugging scenarios.

**Implementation Notes**:  
Care must be taken when reverting changes to avoid losing valuable work or introducing new issues.

